<main>
    <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer1')">How do I create a new exam form?</h2>
        <div id="answer1" class="answer">
            <p>To create a new exam form, log in to your account and navigate to the 'Create Exam' section. Follow the
                on-screen instructions to fill in the details, set up questions, and configure exam settings. Once
                done, save the form, and it will be ready for use.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer2')">Can I edit an already created exam form?</h2>
        <div id="answer2" class="answer">
            <p>Yes, you can edit an existing exam form. Go to the 'Manage Exams' section, find the exam form you want to
                edit, and click on the 'Edit' button. Make the necessary changes and save the form to update it.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer3')">How can I view exam results?</h2>
        <div id="answer3" class="answer">
            <p>To view exam results, navigate to the 'Results' tab on your dashboard. You will find a list of
                completed exams with corresponding result details. Click on a specific exam to view detailed results
                and analytics.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer4')">How do I invite students to take an exam?</h2>
<div id="answer4" class="answer">
    <p>To invite students to take an exam, go to the 'Manage Exams' section, find the desired exam, and click on the
        'Invite Students' button. You can then select students or share a unique link for them to access the exam.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer5')">What types of questions can I include in an exam form?</h2>
<div id="answer5" class="answer">
    <p>You can include various question types such as multiple-choice, true/false, short answer, and essay questions
        in your exam form. Choose the appropriate question type when creating or editing the questions for your exam.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer6')">Is there a limit to the number of students who can take an exam?</h2>
<div id="answer6" class="answer">
    <p>No, there is no strict limit on the number of students who can take an exam. However, consider the technical
        specifications and server capacity to ensure a smooth experience for all participants.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Additional FAQ sections -->
<div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer7')">How can I schedule exams for a specific date and time?</h2>
<div id="answer7" class="answer">
    <p>To schedule exams, navigate to the 'Schedule Exams' section in your dashboard. Choose the exam you want to
        schedule, and set the date and time parameters. The system will automatically handle exam availability based
        on your settings.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer8')">Can I customize the appearance of the exam forms?</h2>
<div id="answer8" class="answer">
    <p>Yes, you can customize the appearance of your exam forms. In the 'Form Settings' or 'Design' section, you can
        modify colors, fonts, and add branding elements to match your institution's or organization's visual
        identity.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-section">
<h2 class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer9')">What security measures are in place to prevent cheating during exams?</h2>
<div id="answer9" class="answer">
    <p>The Exam Portal employs various security measures, including randomizing question order, time limits, and
        anti-cheating algorithms. Additionally, the system may support features like secure browser mode to minimize
        cheating possibilities.</p>
</div>
</div>

